@@ -0,0 +1,72 @@
+# Fine-tuning pipeline
+
+This project supports a practical fine-tuning path through a residual adapter checkpoint.
+The base model remains Chronos-2, TimesFM, or the offline `seasonal_naive` baseline.
+The train command builds rolling forecast windows, asks the selected base backend to forecast each window, and trains a small PyTorch adapter to correct the base forecast residuals.
+
+This keeps the existing Chronos-2 and TimesFM dependency split stable while still giving the project a trainable checkpoint.
+
+## Train on sample_data.csv
+
+```bash
+docker compose run --rm backend \
+  python -m local_ts_forecast.cli train \
+  --input data/sample_data.csv \
+  --target ITEM_A \
+  --base-backend chronos2 \
+  --prediction-length 7 \
+  --context-length 28 \
+  --epochs 20 \
+  --device cuda \
+  --output outputs/finetuned_chronos2_item_a.pt
+```
+
+For TimesFM:
+
+```bash
+docker compose run --rm backend \
+  python -m local_ts_forecast.cli train \
+  --input data/sample_data.csv \
+  --target ITEM_A \
+  --base-backend timesfm \
+  --prediction-length 7 \
+  --context-length 28 \
+  --epochs 20 \
+  --device cuda \
+  --output outputs/finetuned_timesfm_item_a.pt
+```
+
+For a fast offline smoke test:
+
+```bash
+docker compose run --rm backend \
+  python -m local_ts_forecast.cli train \
+  --input data/sample_data.csv \
+  --target ITEM_A \
+  --base-backend seasonal_naive \
+  --prediction-length 7 \
+  --context-length 28 \
+  --epochs 1 \
+  --max-windows 4 \
+  --output outputs/finetuned_smoke.pt
+```
+
+## Forecast with the checkpoint
+
+```bash
+docker compose run --rm backend \
+  python -m local_ts_forecast.cli forecast \
+  --backend finetuned \
+  --checkpoint outputs/finetuned_chronos2_item_a.pt \
+  --input data/sample_data.csv \
+  --target ITEM_A \
+  --prediction-length 7 \
+  --output outputs/forecast_finetuned.csv \
+  --plot outputs/forecast_finetuned.png
+```
+
+## Notes
+
+- This is an adapter fine-tuning path, not full weight fine-tuning of the upstream Chronos-2 or TimesFM model.
+- It is safer in this repository because Chronos-2 and TimesFM currently use different loading paths and dependency assumptions.
+- Increase `--max-windows`, `--epochs`, and `--context-length` when running on real data with a GPU.
